<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-684-925  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 684 925.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 27 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>French unveil prototype videophone. (France Telecom)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dauchy, Eric.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   France Telecom (Product development).andO;Topic:     Product developmentVideo TelephonesTelecommunicationsFrancePrototype.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>FRENCH UNVEIL PROTOTYPE VIDEOPHONE 11/27/90 PARIS, FRANCE, 1990 NOV 27 (NB)-- France Telecom, the state-controlled telephone company, unveiled aprototype videophone which it claims is more advanced than its Japanesecounterpart.andP;  Capable of transmitting voice, data, and color-TV images, it isset to enter the market next year, French PTT Minister Paul Quiles said.andM;At a unit price of 30,000 FF ($6,000) and for home use by 1995 at the stiffgoing price of $ 5,000, it was designed as a European alternative to Japaneseprojects which are in an advanced stage.andM;Nippon Telegraph andamp; Telephone claimed that its Visual, Intelligent andamp; Personalservices will &quot;enable voice, visual or data communications anywhere anytime&quot;including #D, High-Definition visual communications services, amachine-translation-assisted service, a confidential intelligentcommunication service and a portable directory.andP;  NTT predicted that &quot;withinthe next 15 years there will be 15 million pocket phone users, 20 millione-mail subscribers, five million visiphone customers and 20 million digitizedsubscriber access lines.&quot;andM;For France meanwhile the videophone is of strategic importance to remain onthe forefront in telecom technology.andP;  &quot;We must develop an offensive strategyof telecommunications technology development,&quot; Quiles told reporters.andP;  Francesubsidizes a multibillion franc HDTV project undertaken by Thomson SA andDutch electronics manufacturer Philips NV.andP;  Currently, the country haspledged to support heavily mobile telephone technology, another potentialboomer expected to rise significantly before the end of the century.andM;By the end of 1992, France Telecom is expected to order 100,000 videophonesets for sale to mass market consumers.andP;  It expects producers to take twoyears to start providing marketable units for the general public, it said.andM;Matra of France has acquired a license to produce the videophone which theFrench hope to use as a springboard to promote other telephone products &quot;Madein France&quot; such as mobile telephones and pocket phones.andM;(Eric Dauchy/19901126)</TEXT></DOC>